description:
&lt;p&gt;The programme is designed to enable practitioners to adopt a strategic approach to the provision of specialist community nursing care, working effectively with individuals, families, groups and communities, involving, where appropriate, an active collaboration with other disciplines and agencies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It fulfills the professional standards for the education and preparation of specialist community practitioners developed by the UKCC [2001] and is endorsed by the Nursing and Midwifery Council. The programme leads to a professional recognition in community children’s nursing, community nursing in the home – district nursing or general practice nursing preparing students for an enhanced, specialist role with specific patient/client groups in the community with either an Independent Nurse prescribing award or community nurse prescribing award. The programme also prepares specialist community practitioners to effectively contribute to the current health policy agenda through the provision of quality specialist community nursing interventions that promote the health and well-being of individuals, families, groups and communities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Who’s the course for?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The course is suitable for all registered nurses who want to enhance their skills and advance their knowledge in community nursing in order to achieve recognition with the Nursing and Midwifery Council as a Specialist Community Practitioner in District, General Practice or Community Children’s Nursing. Applicants are normally sponsored or seconded by a Primary Care organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Where shall I study?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The course takes place at either the College Lane, De Havilland or Meridian House campuses in Hatfield, just 25-minutes away from Central London by train. Luton airport and Stansted airport are just 40 minutes away.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Where will my community placement be?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your community will be with the Children&#39;s Community Nursing Team at East and North Hertfordshire NHS Trust. This exciting opportunity has developed as part of a strong supportive relationship with fantastic Hertfordshire Community Nurses Charity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will provide above and beyond the already CQC rated ‘Outstanding care’ and support to Children and Young People across East and North Hertfordshire with various acute and chronic health needs. If you are an experienced, dynamic and motivated Paediatric Nurse who is committed to pushing levels of care and experience to be the best it can for every Child and young person then we want to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will work closely with the Children’s Community Nursing team, Special School Nursing Team and Continuing Care Team across the many sites of the trust. The key role objectives will be to; Provide a faster transition from hospital to home to school, Provide increased support to patients and their families, Provide a specialised patient experience&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A key focus of this role will be on measuring its impact. You will need to review, evaluate and evolve the role accordingly to ensure it has the biggest influence possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are as excited as we are about this exclusive opportunity please make contact for an informal discussion and apply to work with East and North Hertfordshire Children’s Community Nursing services in partnership with Hertfordshire Community Nurses Charity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details, informal visit/discussion, please call;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Elizabeth Bessell - Deputy Nursing Service Manager - Community Paediatrics&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07920235986&lt;/p&gt;
